# ❤️ Heart Disease Prediction App

An AI-powered web application that predicts the risk of heart disease based on patient health parameters.

## 🚀 Overview
This project uses Machine Learning to analyze patient data and classify whether a person is at risk of heart disease.

The application is built using:
- Python
- Machine Learning (Scikit-learn)
- Streamlit (for UI)

---

## ⚙️ Features
- User-friendly interface
- Real-time prediction
- Confidence score display
- Clean and structured UI

---

## 🧠 Machine Learning Models Used
- Logistic Regression
- Decision Tree
- Random Forest (Selected Best Model)

---

## 📊 Input Parameters
- Age
- Sex
- Chest Pain Type
- Resting Blood Pressure
- Cholesterol
- Max Heart Rate
- Oldpeak (Heart Stress Level)
- Number of Major Vessels

---

## 🧪 Model Evaluation
- Accuracy Score
- Confusion Matrix
- Classification Report
- Precision, Recall, F1 Score

---

## 🏆 Best Model
Random Forest performed best based on accuracy and evaluation metrics.

